widgets_values:
Mask is generated by the BBOX node and scaled to 1024x1024 so we can produce a high quality close up render of the face.

If you look at the 'Mask To Region' node you may want to play with the 'padding' value. By default this is set to 128 which gives more room for the render to derive context surrounding the face. A higher padding results in a more natural output but will reduce the quality. 128 seems like a good starting point.

Mask is generated by the SAM node which we set to 1024x1024 to match the BBOX mask size.

The mask is then taken through a few operations to prepare the mask for combination with our re-rendered face.

1. Force mask resize to 1024x1024 to match BBOX.
2. Blur the face mask to soften hard edges when blending the face with the image.

See: https://github.com/BadCafeCode/masquerade-nodes-comfyui

### Framing

 - full body shot

### Angles

 - straight on

 - side view
 - back view | from behind
 - from above
 - from below
 - wide angle view
 - fisheye view
 - overhead shot
 - top down shot
 - hero view
 - selfie

### Examples

Landscape:

a beautiful woman, medium shot, bilaterally symmetrical, new york city, sunset
a beautiful woman, side view, full body shot, new york city, sunset 
a beautiful woman, hero view, from behind, new york city, sunset 
a beautiful woman, hero view, medium shot, new york city, sunset

a beautiful woman, side view, (close up:1.2), new york city, city streets, sunset

Portrait:

a beautiful woman, near a door, natural light, (medium shot:1.3), (from above:1.5) (front view:1.4)
a beautiful woman, near a window, natural light, (upper body shot:1.3), (bilaterally symmetrical:1.4)
a beautiful woman, near a door, a beautiful woman, near a door, natural light, (full body shot:1.5), (from below:1.6)natural light, (full body shot:1.5), (from above:1.6)

### Note

Certain framing and angle combinations can be in conflict with the desired outcomes. Certain framing are best suited in closer or further zooms and various aspect ratios (landscape vs portrait)
